525
00:48:07,017 --> 00:48:08,610
You live in there?

526
00:48:11,622 --> 00:48:13,021
By yourself?

527
00:48:13,324 --> 00:48:16,055
No. I have a roommate,
but she's not home.

528
00:48:17,628 --> 00:48:18,993
Hey, it's okay.

529
00:48:19,797 --> 00:48:21,822
Listen, no one will bother us.

530
00:48:22,833 --> 00:48:24,358
It's okay. Come on.

531
00:48:25,136 --> 00:48:26,194
Come on.

532
00:48:52,530 --> 00:48:53,759
This is it.

533
00:48:57,868 --> 00:48:59,427
That's a nice tree.

534
00:49:05,709 --> 00:49:09,441
Sorry about the mess.
Maid's day off.

535
00:49:24,261 --> 00:49:25,626
It's...

536
00:49:26,831 --> 00:49:28,595
cozy. It's a...

537
00:49:29,600 --> 00:49:30,931
cozy place.

538
00:49:32,136 --> 00:49:33,467
It's okay.

539
00:49:49,320 --> 00:49:53,689
Do you suppose we
should talk about money?

540
00:49:54,492 --> 00:49:55,960
Yeah, I guess so.

541
00:49:57,595 --> 00:49:59,723
That depends on what you want to do.

542
00:50:04,335 --> 00:50:05,769
What do you want to do?

543
00:50:10,107 --> 00:50:11,802
What do you recommend?

544
00:50:16,647 --> 00:50:18,342
What do I recommend?

545
00:50:32,963 --> 00:50:35,830
I'd rather not put it into words.

546
00:50:38,702 --> 00:50:40,864
How about you just leave it up to me?

547
00:50:41,338 --> 00:50:43,102
I'm in your hands.

548
00:50:46,010 --> 00:50:48,604
And how does 150 sound?

549
00:50:49,613 --> 00:50:52,105
Sounds wonderful.

550
00:50:56,120 --> 00:51:00,023
Don't worry. I don't
keep track of the time.

551
00:51:07,932 --> 00:51:08,932
<i>Thank you.</i>

552
00:51:09,066 --> 00:51:10,066
Prego, prego.

553
00:51:10,267 --> 00:51:12,531
- Grazie.
<i>- You're welcome.</i>

554
00:51:13,470 --> 00:51:15,996
<i>If I was Italian,
he'd have answered me in Italian.</i>

555
00:52:00,284 --> 00:52:01,581
Shall we?

556
00:52:20,037 --> 00:52:21,368
Excuse me.

557
00:52:35,686 --> 00:52:37,484
Is everything all right?

558
00:52:41,325 --> 00:52:44,625
I was just wondering if you
were going to be much longer?

559
00:52:46,230 --> 00:52:51,168
Listen, it's a little difficult
to talk right now.

560
00:52:51,969 --> 00:52:53,801
It could be awhile.

561
00:52:55,339 --> 00:52:57,501
Any idea how long?

562
00:52:58,308 --> 00:53:00,743
No, I don't really know.

563
00:53:01,111 --> 00:53:03,910
We're still waiting
for some relatives to arrive.

564
00:53:05,949 --> 00:53:10,182
Well, I'm gonna go to bed now.

565
00:53:28,539 --> 00:53:32,237
Was that Mrs. Dr. Bill?

566
00:53:52,529 --> 00:53:54,054
Do you have to go?

567
00:53:55,332 --> 00:53:57,460
Do I have to go?

568
00:54:02,139 --> 00:54:03,766
I think I do.

569
00:54:06,577 --> 00:54:08,011
Are you sure?

570
00:54:14,184 --> 00:54:16,414
Yes, I'm afraid so.

571
00:54:19,656 --> 00:54:22,523
But listen,
I want to pay you anyway.

572
00:54:23,093 --> 00:54:27,462
How much did you say it was?
Hundred and fifty?

573
00:54:31,335 --> 00:54:34,896
But you know what?
You don't have to bother about that.

574
00:54:35,139 --> 00:54:36,573
No, it's all right.

575
00:54:37,508 --> 00:54:40,637
- No, really. You don't have to.
- No, I want to.

576
00:54:43,180 --> 00:54:44,180
Really?

577
00:54:46,784 --> 00:54:48,718
Well, thank you very much.

578
00:55:33,497 --> 00:55:34,623
Thank you.

579
00:55:49,146 --> 00:55:52,480
Would you like a table,
or would you like to sit at the bar?

580
00:55:52,683 --> 00:55:55,516
- I'd like a table.
- Please follow me.

581
00:56:03,627 --> 00:56:05,857
- Can I take your coat?
- Thank you.

582
00:56:06,997 --> 00:56:08,988
Could I get you anything to drink?

583
00:56:10,167 --> 00:56:12,534
- I'd like a beer.
- Certainly.

584
00:56:23,280 --> 00:56:25,510
One, two, one-two-three-four.

585
00:56:26,783 --> 00:56:28,979
That's it for tonight,
ladies and gentlemen.

586
00:56:29,186 --> 00:56:33,919
On the bass, Mr. Larry McVey.
On the drums, Kip Fleming.

587
00:56:34,124 --> 00:56:38,220
And on the guitar,
the one, the only, Mr. Bobby Berman.

588
00:56:38,428 --> 00:56:42,626
We'll be here for the next two weeks,
so please do stop by.

589
00:56:42,833 --> 00:56:45,393
I'm Nick Nightingale. Good night.

590
00:56:55,846 --> 00:56:58,406
- Nick, that was great.
- Thanks.

591
00:56:58,749 --> 00:57:02,117
- Nightingale.
- Hey, Bill, you made it.

592
00:57:02,319 --> 00:57:05,812
I'm sorry, I got here just as you
were finishing your last set.

593
00:57:06,023 --> 00:57:09,049
That's all right.
The band sucked tonight anyway.

594
00:57:09,760 --> 00:57:12,923
- What are you drinking?
- A vodka and tonic, please.

595
00:57:14,498 --> 00:57:15,522
Thank you.

596
00:57:17,267 --> 00:57:19,599
So what brings you out at this hour?

597
00:57:19,803 --> 00:57:22,966
- I have a patient in the neighborhood.
- You live in the Village?

598
00:57:23,173 --> 00:57:26,108
No, we have an apartment
on Central Park West.

599
00:57:26,310 --> 00:57:27,675
You're married?

600
00:57:28,345 --> 00:57:29,710
Nine years.

601
00:57:30,113 --> 00:57:33,048
- Any kids?
- Yes, we have a 7-year-old daughter.

602
00:57:33,250 --> 00:57:34,342
How about you?

603
00:57:34,551 --> 00:57:37,145
I've got a wife
and four boys in Seattle.

604
00:57:37,354 --> 00:57:38,788
You're a long way from home.

605
00:57:39,189 --> 00:57:41,886
Well, you gotta go where the work is.

606
00:57:42,693 --> 00:57:43,717
Thank you.

607
00:57:49,800 --> 00:57:52,269
- Is this your band?
- No, it's a pick-up band.

608
00:57:52,469 --> 00:57:56,497
- Who do you normally play with?
- Anybody, anywhere.

609
00:57:56,740 --> 00:57:59,175
I got another gig later tonight.

610
00:57:59,376 --> 00:58:01,310
You're playing somewhere else tonight?

611
00:58:01,511 --> 00:58:03,206
They only get started around 2.

612
00:58:04,047 --> 00:58:05,208
In the Village?

613
00:58:07,417 --> 00:58:10,853
Believe it or not,
I don't actually know the address yet.

614
00:58:11,321 --> 00:58:12,345
You don't?

615
00:58:13,023 --> 00:58:17,722
No. It may sound ridiculous,
but it's in a different place every time,

616
00:58:17,928 --> 00:58:20,761
and I only get it
an hour or so before.

617
00:58:20,964 --> 00:58:23,661
- A different place every time?
- So far.

618
00:58:24,768 --> 00:58:25,997
What's the big mystery?

619
00:58:26,770 --> 00:58:30,035
Hey, man, I just play the piano.

620
00:58:33,744 --> 00:58:36,975
Nick, I'm sorry.
Is there something I'm missing here?

621
00:58:39,983 --> 00:58:42,816
I play blindfolded.

622
00:58:43,954 --> 00:58:45,149
What?

623
00:58:46,957 --> 00:58:49,585
I play blindfolded.

624
00:58:53,630 --> 00:58:55,155
You're putting me on.

625
00:58:55,365 --> 00:58:57,857
No, it's the truth.

626
00:58:58,802 --> 00:59:03,467
And the last time,
the blindfold wasn't on so well.

627
00:59:05,809 --> 00:59:07,573
Oh, man.

628
00:59:08,745 --> 00:59:13,012
Bill, I have seen one or two things
in my life...

629
00:59:13,417 --> 00:59:15,078
but never...

630
00:59:15,452 --> 00:59:17,921
never anything like this...

631
00:59:18,655 --> 00:59:21,716
and never such women.

632
00:59:31,935 --> 00:59:33,232
Excuse me.

633
00:59:37,040 --> 00:59:40,101
Yes, sir.
Yes, sir, this is Nick.

634
00:59:45,982 --> 00:59:47,814
I know where that is.

635
00:59:55,392 --> 00:59:56,392
Right.

636
00:59:59,963 --> 01:00:01,897
Well, I'm on my way right now.

637
01:00:02,666 --> 01:00:05,158
Okay, sir. Thank you.

638
01:00:07,571 --> 01:00:08,936
What is this?

639
01:00:10,474 --> 01:00:13,136
It's the name of a Beethoven opera,
isn't it?

640
01:00:17,948 --> 01:00:19,609
It's the password.

641
01:00:20,317 --> 01:00:21,807
The password?

642
01:00:23,120 --> 01:00:26,750
Yeah. Look. I'm really sorry
to do this to you, Bill.

643
01:00:27,791 --> 01:00:31,625
I gotta get going. I gotta go.

644
01:00:36,666 --> 01:00:40,625
You know there is no way on earth...

645
01:00:41,138 --> 01:00:44,631
that you are going to leave here
without taking me with you.

646
01:00:45,275 --> 01:00:48,973
- Come on, buddy, give me a break.
- Nick, I'll tell you what.

647
01:00:49,179 --> 01:00:52,410
I've already got the password.

648
01:00:53,283 --> 01:00:56,514
Just give me the address.
I'll go there by myself,

649
01:00:56,720 --> 01:01:00,315
and there won't be any connection
between us whatsoever.

650
01:01:02,959 --> 01:01:07,192
Listen, let's just say
for one second...

651
01:01:08,131 --> 01:01:10,293
that I was prepared to do that.

652
01:01:10,700 --> 01:01:13,965
You couldn't get in anyway
in those clothes.

653
01:01:15,205 --> 01:01:16,536
Why not?

654
01:01:17,007 --> 01:01:21,240
Because everyone is always
costumed and masked.

655
01:01:22,112 --> 01:01:25,776
Where the hell are you gonna
get a costume at this hour?

656
01:01:45,702 --> 01:01:47,898
Thanks. Keep the change.

657
01:02:00,984 --> 01:02:03,316
<i>Yes? Who is it?</i>

658
01:02:03,520 --> 01:02:05,284
Peter, this is Bill Harford.

659
01:02:05,488 --> 01:02:09,925
I apologize for disturbing you at this hour,
but I need your help.

660
01:02:11,027 --> 01:02:12,961
<i>Who is it that you want?</i>

661
01:02:14,564 --> 01:02:17,499
I'm very sorry.
I'm looking for Peter Grenning,

662
01:02:17,701 --> 01:02:20,193
the owner of Rainbow Fashions.

663
01:02:22,339 --> 01:02:23,807
<i>What's your name?</i>

664
01:02:24,007 --> 01:02:26,408
My name is Bill Harford.

665
01:02:26,610 --> 01:02:28,806
I'm Mr. Grenning's doctor.

666
01:02:29,813 --> 01:02:31,747
<i>You are Grenning's doctor?</i>

667
01:02:34,884 --> 01:02:36,045
<i>Okay.</i>

668
01:02:36,620 --> 01:02:38,088
<i>Just a moment.</i>

669
01:02:53,270 --> 01:02:55,329
You are looking for Peter Grenning?

670
01:02:55,839 --> 01:02:57,136
Yes, I am.

671
01:02:57,574 --> 01:03:01,477
He moved to Chicago over a year ago.

672
01:03:02,312 --> 01:03:04,508
He moved to Chicago?

673
01:03:07,183 --> 01:03:09,208
I wasn't aware of that.

674
01:03:11,154 --> 01:03:14,749
Then are you the present owner
of Rainbow Fashions?

675
01:03:14,958 --> 01:03:16,585
Yes, I am.

676
01:03:17,027 --> 01:03:18,027
Well, first of all,

677
01:03:18,194 --> 01:03:23,098
please let me apologize again
for disturbing you at this hour, Mr...

678
01:03:23,300 --> 01:03:24,529
Milich.

679
01:03:24,734 --> 01:03:28,898
Mr. Milich. Just to let you know
that I really am Dr. Harford,

680
01:03:29,105 --> 01:03:32,097
this is my
New York State Medical Board card.

681
01:03:33,009 --> 01:03:36,001
Okay, so you are Dr. Harford.

682
01:03:36,212 --> 01:03:39,614
If I see Peter, I tell him
you were looking for him.

683
01:03:39,816 --> 01:03:41,978
Oh, no, wait. Please, please...

684
01:03:42,585 --> 01:03:46,078
Listen, the reason that
I came here tonight was...

685
01:03:48,158 --> 01:03:53,062
Basically, the reason is
that I need a costume.

686
01:03:53,496 --> 01:03:57,330
And I'd be happy to pay you
$100 over the rental price

687
01:03:57,534 --> 01:03:59,127
for the inconvenience.

688
01:04:00,970 --> 01:04:02,301
A hundred dollars?

689
01:04:05,842 --> 01:04:07,503
I don't think so.

690
01:04:10,947 --> 01:04:12,813
How about $200?

691
01:04:13,416 --> 01:04:16,010
Two hundred dollars
over the rental price?

692
01:04:27,864 --> 01:04:29,059
Come in.

693
01:04:33,570 --> 01:04:36,164
Can't be too careful these days.

694
01:04:39,376 --> 01:04:40,502
Please.

695
01:04:43,313 --> 01:04:46,248
Is it any special costume
you are looking for?

696
01:04:49,285 --> 01:04:54,223
I need a tux, a cloak with a hood,
and a mask.

697
01:04:54,691 --> 01:04:57,752
A cloak with a hood and a mask?

698
01:05:01,598 --> 01:05:04,158
I think we'll find something for you.

699
01:05:04,934 --> 01:05:06,561
Follow me, please.

700
01:05:07,137 --> 01:05:08,137
Good.

701
01:05:17,080 --> 01:05:19,242
Looks like alive, huh?

702
01:05:21,017 --> 01:05:23,008
- It's wonderful.
- Come.

703
01:05:24,087 --> 01:05:26,317
So what color cloak?

704
01:05:27,791 --> 01:05:29,486
Red, brown, red?

705
01:05:30,894 --> 01:05:31,986
Black.

706
01:05:32,195 --> 01:05:35,688
The good doctor wouldn't
like something more colorful?

707
01:05:35,899 --> 01:05:38,596
- I don't think so.
- Clowns, officers, pirates?

708
01:05:38,802 --> 01:05:41,464
No, just the tux, the black cloak--

709
01:05:41,671 --> 01:05:43,901
With a hood and a mask.

710
01:05:46,342 --> 01:05:47,867
May I take your coat?

711
01:05:49,746 --> 01:05:53,046
- You are medicine doctor, yes?
- Yes, I am.

712
01:05:54,017 --> 01:05:57,851
- I have some problem with my hair.
- Your hair?

713
01:05:58,054 --> 01:06:00,113
It's starting to fall down too fast.

714
01:06:00,323 --> 01:06:03,258
I lost, in two weeks, a lot of hair.
Mostly here.

715
01:06:03,460 --> 01:06:05,451
Look at this. Here.

716
01:06:06,796 --> 01:06:07,888
You see?

717
01:06:08,598 --> 01:06:09,759
And?

718
01:06:10,633 --> 01:06:12,931
I'm afraid this really isn't my field.

719
01:06:13,136 --> 01:06:15,104
What? You can't help me?

720
01:06:15,305 --> 01:06:18,900
No. You should see a trichologist.
It's a hair specialist.

721
01:06:19,108 --> 01:06:22,738
Mr. Milich, I've obviously
left things a bit late tonight.

722
01:06:22,946 --> 01:06:24,675
So if you don't mind--

723
01:06:24,881 --> 01:06:26,940
I'm in hurry too, to get back to bed.

724
01:06:27,150 --> 01:06:28,481
I understand.

725
01:06:29,486 --> 01:06:31,011
So black cloak?

726
01:06:35,959 --> 01:06:37,358
Did you hear something?

727
01:06:40,663 --> 01:06:42,256
What is this?

728
01:06:51,941 --> 01:06:53,773
What is it?

729
01:06:58,882 --> 01:07:00,850
What is this?

730
01:07:14,564 --> 01:07:17,226
What on earth is going on here?!

731
01:07:17,433 --> 01:07:19,561
Milich, I can explain everything.

732
01:07:19,769 --> 01:07:22,067
You! What are you doing here?

733
01:07:22,272 --> 01:07:24,070
I promise I'll kill you!

734
01:07:24,274 --> 01:07:28,177
And you!
Have you no sense of decency?

735
01:07:28,378 --> 01:07:32,212
Gentlemen, have you
no sense of decency?!

736
01:07:32,415 --> 01:07:36,045
Milich, are you crazy?
We were invited here by the young lady.

737
01:07:36,252 --> 01:07:40,621
Young lady? This is my daughter!
Couldn't you see she's a child?

738
01:07:40,823 --> 01:07:43,622
- You will have to explain to police!
- To the police?!

739
01:07:43,826 --> 01:07:46,693
You little whore!
I kill you for this.

740
01:07:46,896 --> 01:07:50,423
I promise, I'll kill you!
I'll kill you!

741
01:07:50,633 --> 01:07:52,829
Hold on to that girl for me, please!

742
01:07:53,036 --> 01:07:56,995
Milich, this is preposterous.
The young lady invited us here.

743
01:07:57,206 --> 01:07:59,300
Couldn't you see she is deranged?!

744
01:07:59,509 --> 01:08:01,170
Doctor, I'm sorry to keep you waiting.

745
01:08:01,377 --> 01:08:04,176
Gentlemen, this is now a police matter.

746
01:08:04,380 --> 01:08:06,974
You will please stay here
until I return.

747
01:08:07,183 --> 01:08:08,844
Let us out of here!

748
01:08:09,052 --> 01:08:10,986
That's out of the question.

749
01:08:11,187 --> 01:08:14,817
Doctor, sorry.
What color did you say?

750
01:08:15,024 --> 01:08:16,617
- Black?
- Black.

751
01:08:17,226 --> 01:08:20,856
Gentlemen, please have the goodness
to be quiet for the moment!

752
01:08:21,064 --> 01:08:23,328
Couldn't you see
I try to serve my customer?

753
01:08:23,533 --> 01:08:24,533
Sorry.

754
01:08:25,068 --> 01:08:28,629
And you, little whore,
go to bed at once, you depraved creature.

755
01:08:28,838 --> 01:08:31,273
I'll deal with you
after I serve this gentleman.

756
01:08:32,008 --> 01:08:34,807
You should have a cloak
lined with ermine.

757
01:10:21,684 --> 01:10:23,812
Okay, that's $74.50.

758
01:10:24,520 --> 01:10:28,388
Seventy-four fifty. All right.

759
01:10:29,559 --> 01:10:31,084
There's 80.

760
01:10:31,527 --> 01:10:34,428
I promised you 50 bucks
over the meter, right?

761
01:10:36,733 --> 01:10:40,135
I'll make that a hundred,
if you wait for me.

762
01:10:40,336 --> 01:10:41,895
Just let the meter run.

763
01:10:42,105 --> 01:10:45,473
I'll give you the other half
plus the meter when I get back.

764
01:10:45,675 --> 01:10:48,303
- Okay?
- How long you gonna be?

765
01:10:48,511 --> 01:10:51,913
I don't know, maybe an hour or more.
But maybe only 10 minutes.

766
01:10:53,149 --> 01:10:55,083
I'll leave my stuff here in the back.

767
01:11:12,935 --> 01:11:14,334
Good evening, sir.

768
01:11:15,271 --> 01:11:16,568
Good evening.

769
01:11:17,206 --> 01:11:18,571
Can we be of any help?

770
01:11:20,309 --> 01:11:22,209
I suppose you'd like the password.

771
01:11:22,478 --> 01:11:24,037
If you'd like, sir.

772
01:11:24,480 --> 01:11:25,460
Fidelio.

773
01:11:25,515 --> 01:11:28,610
Thank you, sir.
We'll run you up to the house.

774
01:12:08,691 --> 01:12:10,352
Good evening, sir.

775
01:12:10,560 --> 01:12:11,891
Good evening.

776
01:12:12,261 --> 01:12:13,786
Password, sir?

777
01:12:14,664 --> 01:12:15,664
Fidelio.

778
01:12:16,199 --> 01:12:17,667
Thank you, sir.

779
01:18:23,098 --> 01:18:26,068
I'm not sure what you
think you're doing.

780
